           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            
            <div class="ArticleContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/taler_artikler/utenriksministeren/2010/nettverk_arkhangelsk.html?id=614486" title="">
                        Opening remarks at Norwegian-Russian network meeting
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none">Arkhangelsk, 17 September 2010</h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Speech/article, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 17.09.2010]</p>
                <p>“I hope the bilateral agreement on issues at sea, signed this week between our two countries, will also serve as an inspiration for agreement between business partners. Patience, time, negotiations and rethinking of acclaimed truths may be necessary. But the rewards will be worth it”, Foreign Minister Støre said in Arkhangelsk on 17 Sepbember 2010.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp1911044452_wp2011366416_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl02_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/taler_artikler/utenriksministeren/2010/northern_knowledge.html?id=614593" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/UD/Ingressbilder/jgs_arkhangelsk_delelinje.jpg" alt="Jonas Gahr Støre in Arkhangelsk 17 September 2010. Photo: M.Kopstad/MFA" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/ud/aktuelt/taler_artikler/utenriksministeren/2010/northern_knowledge.html?id=614593" title="">
                        Norway and Russia. Taking Northern Knowledge to the Next Level
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none">Northern Arctic Federal University, Arkhangelsk, 17 September 2010. </h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Speech/article, Ministry of Foreign Affairs, 17.09.2010]</p>
                <p>"Developments in the High North must be based on knowledge. This is vital for sustainability and stability. I believe we should build a northern hub of knowledge. The enhanced cooperation between Russian universities and scientific institutions and their Norwegian counterparts is an important part of this", Foreign Minister Støre said in his speech at the Northern Arctic Federal University in Arkhangelsk on 17 September 2010.      </p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp1911044452_wp2011366416_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl03_Label1"></span>                 
           </div>
        </div> 
    
        <div class="ArticleView"> 
            <a href="/en/dep/smk/press-center/Press-releases/2010/treaty.html?id=614254" class="ISI_IGNORE">
                <img src="/upload/SMK/Nyhetsbilder/2010/avtale_store.gif" alt="" class="ArticleImg" />
            </a>
            <div class="ArticleImgContent">
                <h2>
                    <a href="/en/dep/smk/press-center/Press-releases/2010/treaty.html?id=614254" title="">
                        Treaty on maritime delimitation and cooperation in the Barents Sea and the Arctic Ocean signed today
                    </a>
                </h2>
                <h3 class="subDescription" style="display:none"></h3>
                <p class="ArticleInfo">[Press release, The Office of the Prime Minister, 15.09.2010]</p>
                <p>Norway and Russia signed the treaty on maritime delimitation and cooperation in the Barents Sea and the Arctic Ocean in Murmansk today. It was signed by Foreign Ministers Jonas Gahr Støre and Sergei Lavrov in the presence of Prime Minister Jens Stoltenberg and President Dmitry Medvedev.</p>
                
                
                <p>
                    
                    
                </p>
                <span id="ctl00_FullRegion_CenterAndRightRegion_CenterRegion_SubjectManager_wp1911044452_wp2011366416_lstSearchResult_lstUniversal_ctl04_Label1"></span>                 
